THE subject of this Satire is a quarrel between the people of Ombos and those of Tentyra, two towns in the Nile valley situate about 1oo miles irom one another. It appears a little strained in Juvenal to call these two towns neighbours; but it must be remembered that their districts would extend further than the towns, and the distance between the two as the crow flies is less than seventv miles.
